       <div class="block block-views collapse-mobile" id="block-views-tufts-in-the-news-block">
        <h2 class="title">
         Tufts in the News
        </h2>
        <div class="content">
         <!--googleoff: index-->
         <div class="view view-tufts-in-the-news view-id-tufts_in_the_news view-display-id-block view-dom-id-b2199c0c4c180aa3843fe6895202b8b7">
          <div class="view-content">
           <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first clearfix">
            <div class="views-field views-field-field-publish-date">
             <div class="field-content">
              <span class="date-display-single" content="2019-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" property="dc:date">
               Feb 21, 2019
              </span>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="views-field views-field-field-publication-source">
             <div class="field-content">
              <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/21/arts/design/black-history-african-american-trail-project-boston.html">
               New York Times
              </a>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="views-field views-field-title">
             <span class="field-content">
              Black History Trail Makes 200 Stops Across Massachusetts
             </span>
            </div>
            <div class="views-field views-field-field-tin-description">
             <div class="field-content">
              Tufts historian Kendra Field and lecturer Kerri Greenidge developed a website called the African American Trail Project from their research tracing the history of Massachusetts’ African American residents. The article links to the website and features four of the more than 200 historic sites.
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
           <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even clearfix">
            <div class="views-field views-field-field-publish-date">
             <div class="field-content">
              <span class="date-display-single" content="2019-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" property="dc:date">
               Feb 19, 2019
              </span>
             </div>
            </div>
